<p>To determine an appropriate sample size <i>n</i> for estimating proporti=
ons, the equation below can be solved, where W represents the desired width=
 of the confidence interval. The resulting sample size formula, is often ap=
plied with a conservative estimate of <i>p</i> (e.g., 0.5):
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e Z{\sqrt {\frac {0.25}{n}}}=3DW/2}">
