-align: -2.838ex; width:23.451ex; height:6.509ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle \l=
eft({\bar {x}}-{\frac {Z\sigma }{\sqrt {n}}},\quad {\bar {x}}+{\frac {Z\sig=
ma }{\sqrt {n}}}\right)}"></span> ,</dd>
<dd>where Z is a standard <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Standard=
_score" title=3D"Standard score">Z-score</a> for the desired level of confi=
dence (1.96 for a 95% confidence interval).</dd></dl>
<p>To determine the sample size <i>n</i> required for a confidence interval=
 of width W, with W/2 as the margin of error on each side of the sample mea=
n, the equation
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e {\frac {Z\sigma }{\sqrt {n}}}=3DW/2}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
