-align: -2.838ex; width:12.025ex; height:6.176ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle {\=
frac {Z\sigma }{\sqrt {n}}}=3DW/2}"></span> can be solved. This yields the =
sample size formula, for <i>n</i>:</dd></dl>
<p><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"=
mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math=
 xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle n=
=3D{\frac {4Z^{2}\sigma ^{2}}{W^{2}}}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
