    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle n=3D{\frac {4=
Z^{2}\sigma ^{2}}{W^{2}}}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/edd8ef9b0e55be91cdca4ff21e67fb17dd00fa3e" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -2.171ex; width:11.639ex; height:6.009ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle n=
=3D{\frac {4Z^{2}\sigma ^{2}}{W^{2}}}}"></span><i>.</i>
</p><p>For instance, if estimating the effect of a drug on blood pressure w=
ith a 95% confidence interval that is six units wide, and the known standar=
d deviation of blood pressure in the population is 15, the required sample =
size would be <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><spa=
n class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: n=
one;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displ=
aystyle {\frac {4\times 1.96^{2}\times 15^{2}}{6^{2}}}=3D96.04}">
  <semantics>
